<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-27T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-27T09:00:00-05:00" n="646" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d646">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2815</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-27T16:00:00+02:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 27, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 28, 12.32
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2054. Department’s circular of September 20, 6 p.m., terrorism in
                                Russia, only received September 24 from Paris. It was immediately
                                brought to the attention of Foreign Office which replies to-day:
                                “Italian Government adheres fully to the views of the United States
                                Government.”</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>